      <description>&lt;p&gt;I will be joining in the first semester of 2020 as professor of economics at the School of Economics, Business and Accounting of University of São Paulo (FEA-USP).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previously, I have been post-doctoral researcher at the Pontifical Catholic University of Rio de Janeiro (2016-2018, with a Capes scholarship) and at USP (2018-2020, with a Fapesp scholarship). In 2014 I was a visiting scholar at the Harvard Kennedy School of Government (Capes scholarship).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My research interests include patronage and the efficiency of municipal bureaucracry and optimal social insurance and taxation in developing economies. As hobbies, I like to play capoeira, rowing, and literature. Also, I have a wonderful wife and a cute baby son.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
